# NOTE (FEN-471): this pattern is INERT under pnpm 11.5.0 — it does NOT place
# @better-auth/* in the ROOT node_modules (they land only in the hidden
# .pnpm/node_modules/, which is off Node's runtime resolution path). It is kept
# only as defense-in-depth and is NOT relied upon.
#
# The REAL guarantee that the SSR-externalized auth deps resolve at runtime is
# that they are declared as DIRECT dependencies in package.json
# (@better-auth/core, @better-auth/kysely-adapter, @better-auth/telemetry,
# @better-auth/utils, kysely). pnpm always materialises a direct dep at root
# node_modules regardless of hoist settings, and direct prod deps survive
# `pnpm prune --prod` in Dockerfile.app deterministically. See vite.config.ts.
public-hoist-pattern[]=@better-auth/*
